727952f-a.text:
St. Nicholas Ave., north side, west of Woodbine Street. Note,white stuccoed structures at right extending to Palmetto Street (elevated line thereon) are on site of old carbarns and are now known as the Ridgewood
Grove, a place of amusement..
September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
